{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/dealing-with-linux-files-via-inode","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"e1f0b07c-2714-5206-96c8-3b2e722b7436","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/4b190/filesystem.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/8ac56/filesystem.webp 240w,\n/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/d3be9/filesystem.webp 480w,\n/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/d00b9/filesystem.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/09b79/filesystem.jpg 240w,\n/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/7cc5e/filesystem.jpg 480w,\n/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/4b190/filesystem.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/4b190/filesystem.jpg\"\n            alt=\"file system\"\n            title=\"file system\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>In the UNIX/Linux system, name-garbled files are generated in some cases. Itâ€™s hard to operate on such kind of files via their file names.</p>\n<p>Based on the implementation of the UNIX/Linux file system, each file is associated with inodes. We can operate on any file with inode as an alternative.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Get the inode of the name-garbled file</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ <span class=\"token function\">ls</span> -il\ntotal <span class=\"token number\">125252</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>.\n<span class=\"token number\">200556696</span> -rwxr-xr-x <span class=\"token number\">1</span> x x <span class=\"token number\">676</span> Mar <span class=\"token number\">30</span> <span class=\"token number\">15</span>:20 common.sh\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">..</span>.</code></pre></div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Process files based on the inode, for example, delete</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\"><pre class=\"language-bash\"><code class=\"language-bash\">$ find. -inum <span class=\"token number\">200556696</span> -exec <span class=\"token function\">rm</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">\\</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n</li>\n</ol>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/dealing-with-linux-files-via-inode","tagSlugs":["/tag/linux-system/","/tag/file-system/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2012-03-30T17:35:00.000Z","description":"dealing with linux file with inode is an important alternative.","tags":["Linux System","File System"],"title":"Dealing with Linux Files via inode","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/7e66bce6f2577126360c225f8569c666/filesystem.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/dealing-with-linux-files-via-inode"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}